using System;
using System.Collections.Generic;

namespace OpenClawTray.Helpers;

/// <summary>
/// Lookup tables for the Hub <c>NavigationView</c> sidebar icons used by
/// <c>HubWindow</c>. Maps each <c>NavigationViewItem.Tag</c> to:
/// <list type="bullet">
///   <item>A colorful SVG resource key (e.g. <c>"chat" → "Chat_Icon"</c>),
///         looked up against the <c>NavigationView.Resources</c> dictionary
///         defined in <c>HubWindow.xaml</c>.</item>
///   <item>An SVG path "d" string used as the monochrome variant (rendered
///         via <c>PathIcon</c> so the foreground brush inherits the current
///         theme / High Contrast color). The path data is derived from the
///         matching "regular" variant of the <c>microsoft/fluentui-system-icons</c>
///         SVG and kept in sync with the on-disk files under
///         <c>Assets/SidebarIcons/Mono/</c> (see <c>SidebarIconCatalogTests</c>).</item>
/// </list>
/// Centralized here so tests can assert that every sidebar tag is covered.
/// </summary>
public static class SidebarIconCatalog
{
